      "content": "that's a good list. but i'm wondering about the \"global wardrobe\" and \"language\" parts. it sounds very much like a western business standard—you know, the suit and tie look and a certain way of speaking. if i'm writing for a truly global audience, why is that specific style the benchmark for \"sophistication\"? wouldn't someone in Lagos or Mumbai or Singapore have their own versions of \"professional\" clothing or \"poised\" communication that are just as high-status?",
