      "content": "You're right, the Western business standard is not universal, and what constitutes \"sophistication\" can vary greatly across cultures. A more inclusive approach would be to focus on timeless, versatile pieces that can be adapted to different cultural contexts, such as a well-fitted, high-quality suit, a simple yet elegant watch, and a pair of polished, leather shoes. For \"language of luxury,\" you could explore the concept of \"soft power\" and the importance of being articulate, yet humble, in your communication style. This could involve discussing the value of active listening, using clear and concise language, and avoiding jargon or overly technical terms that might be alienating. By focusing on these universal qualities, you can create a guide that is more relatable and applicable to a diverse global audience.",
